cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of designing models that can handle images from different visual domains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture for multi-domain learning, which involves training a model to work on new domains with less resources. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also introduces a gating mechanism to promote soft sharing between different domains, which could place it in the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a benchmark for testing the ability of multi-domain models, which could place it in the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
